column31: Hey, friends. I hope you're all keeping well. Looking for some guidance. I think I may have MS (Multiple Sclerosis). I've gone to my GP about this but keep getting dismissed. My symptoms began about 2 years ago, but recently new symtoms have emerged. So, about 2 years ago I began experiencing a tingly, pins and needles sensation in my head. Months later, those sensations emerged all down my spine, then a further few months later I began experiencing the same sensations in my limbs and extremities - that's when it really started to bother me. It felt like whatever I was experiencing was progressive and degenerative. Back then, I thought my symptoms were due to a B12 deficiency. I just kind of ignored it, until about 3 months ago when I started taking a B12 supplement and even changed my diet from vegan to a non-vegan 'traditional diet'. It was the progression of symptoms to the limbs and extremities that really freaked me out and kick-started me into taking action. There were a few occasions when I lost almost all sensation in my right arm and hand, finding it hard to grasp things and generally feeling 'dead' in the arm/hand. That particular issue really frightened me. Now, about a month ago, I began experiencing random muscle twitches/spasms around my body. They'd happen very quickly. They feel like little muscular flutters. Then even more recently (a matter of days ago), I began experiencing this sharp, stabbing, pulling sensation in various locations around my body. These seem to have replaced the muscle twitches, because I don't notice those much anymore since experiencing these sharp twangs. In addition to this (and this is the most direstessing symptom), I have recently (in the past few days) started expericing this horrible head sensation that I can only describe as a mixture between dizziness, light-headedness and a head rush. It's not affected by motion and it doesn't involve 'spinning', as such. It's more a sensation of something swishy or 'woozy' going on inside my brain. I actually first noticed this a few months ago, where I'd experience it for about a second every few days. Then about 3 days ago, I'd experice it several times an hour. As of today, I've spent most of the day in a constant state of 'head rush', resulting in nausea and an ability to do daily things. I'm keen to have this investigated, even if I have to go private. But, just based on what I've described, does anyone have any advice or guidance for me? The head rush sensation is the most distressing, at the moment.

Plants aren’t just coated with pesticides, plants soak up pesticides; root vegetables in particular are vulnerable as well as fruits and veggies with thin “skins” as they lack the proper physical barriers needed for protection. No matter how much you wash them you can’t get rid of the pesticides that are now throughout your food.

column36:
Just one more reason I distrust gov't and all the agencies in charge of our food supplies.
~
New government report finds "toxic heavy metals"
 like arsenic and mercury in popular baby foods
Baby food from several of the country's largest manufacturers are "tainted" with toxic heavy metals, according to a disturbing new government report. 

The report, released Thursday morning, says those baby foods have "significant levels" of substances including lead, arsenic, cadmium and mercury. The metals can be especially dangerous to babies' and toddlers' brain development. 

Parents often say they are looking for the healthiest, safest food for their babies. But as Connecticut mom Carrie Kerner found out, it's difficult to look for something you may not even be aware of.

"I just looked for the ingredients," Kerner told CBS News consumer investigative correspondent Anna Werner. "If there was any added preservatives, sweeteners or added sugars, I wouldn't buy it, so I basically just wanted to get organic."

Kerner had her first child, Chloe, a year ago. Ever since, she said she has been paying close attention to what is in Chloe's food.

But one thing Kerner and her husband Bryan, who is a doctor, never worried about was whether the baby food contained toxic metals.

She said the revelation was "very concerning as a new mom."

"That's the least thing a mother wants to think about. You're already worrying about her choking — about what goes into these foods," Kerner said.

Yet a new congressional subcommittee investigation found major concerns over the presence of metals in baby food. The report says "baby foods are tainted with dangerous levels" of "toxic heavy metals, including arsenic, lead, cadmium and mercury."

Researchers say that developing brains of babies and young children are "uniquely vulnerable" to toxic chemicals, which can cause "permanent brain injury." Troubling risks include lowering IQ, problems in school and even criminal behavior later in life. 

Illinois Democratic Rep. Raja Krishnamoorthi told CBS News that getting heavy metals out of food sold for infants is critical.

"I don't know a mom or dad that wants neurotoxins in their babies' foods," he said.

Investigators asked seven U.S. baby food manufacturers to provide internal documents and test results. 

Of the four that did, all showed the presence of lead, arsenic and cadmium in their own test results — at levels the report says "eclipse" maximum levels set for other products.

Compared to the levels allowed by the FDA in bottled water, the report claimed, the results were "up to 91 times the arsenic level," "up to 69 times the cadmium level," and "up to 177 times the lead level."

CBS News asked those companies for comment, and all who responded said they are committed to safety. 

All the companies that responded also said they either comply with government standards, have developed their own internal quality and testing standards, or both. Several said they are part of the Baby Food Council, a group formed with the goal of voluntarily reducing heavy metals in baby foods.

The problem is not new, however — Consumer Reports did its own testing of 50 nationally-distributed baby foods in 2018, finding "every product had measurable levels of at least one" of three heavy metals, and 68% "had worrisome levels of at least one heavy metal."

Consumer Reports' James Dickerson says there's not too much cause for alarm, since these heavy metals are naturally occurring.

"That's the real big issue. You want to minimize the risk, you can't eliminate it entirely, but you can minimize it. And there are steps that we can take," Dickerson said.

He tells parents to limit rice and sweet potato products, which tend to absorb more pollutants because of the way they are grown. Dickerson also recommends avoiding snacks like crackers and puffs, which in Consumer Reports' investigation had higher levels of heavy metals, and vary their child's diet.

Congressman Krishnamoorthi believes that voluntary entry efforts are not enough. He plans to introduce legislation to step up FDA oversight.

"So now we need the FDA to step into the breach and do what I think the American people believe it is, is its job to do," he said. "Which is to make sure that the food that their babies consume is safe."

For worried parents wondering if they should throw out their baby food — experts say no, there is no need to panic if the products are in the pantry, and that the key is moderation. 

When asked for a response, the FDA said it has been working on reducing exposure to toxic elements in foods, but acknowledges there is more work to be done. 

According to Healthy Babies Bright Futures, a group dedicated to "measurably reduce the largest sources of babies' exposures to toxic chemicals," nearly nine out of ten baby foods tested had no enforceable federal safety limit for these heavy metals.

column36:
IS CHINA USING PNG FOR A FUTURE ATTACK ON AUSTRALIA? 

In the Australian newspaper today: 

A Chinese company says it wants to build a new $39bn city with a major seaport, industrial area and free-trade zone on Papua New Guinea’s south coast, just kilometres from Australian territory. 

The “New Daru City” proposal will escalate concerns within Australian security agencies over China’s interest in PNG’s impoverished Western Province, where another Chinese company plans to build a $200m fisheries industrial park. 

Hong Kong-registered WYW Holding, a developer of Myanmar’s New Yangon City, has asked PNG Prime Minister James Marape to approve the development under a “Build Operate Transfer” arrangement, where PNG would receive the assets after an unspecified period of Chinese ownership and management. 

“We hope that you and your government will agree to engage with us on this ambitious plan which is, as you are aware, predicated on an agreed Sovereign Guarantee based on a long-term BOT contract between and for the mutual benefit of both parties,” company chief executive Terrance Mo said in a letter to Mr Marape last April. 

Mr Mo said the proposed city would span 100sq km and include fisheries and agricultural processing facilities, and provision for “intensive manufacturing” . 

In a separate letter, the chairman of WYW Holding, Calvin Ng, told Mr Marape that PNG could “advance significantly through appropriate infrastructure development , modern communications, efficient transport systems and natural resource exploitation” . 

Daru, which has a population of just 20,000 people and is the centre of a multidrug-resistant tuberculosis epidemic, is about 200km from the Australian mainland but within kilometres of Australian islands in the Torres Strait. 

The proposed value of the development would exceed PNG’s annual GDP by about $US5bn. 

The company said funding for the “tremendous investment opportunity” would come from China, Europe, the Middle East, Singapore and Hong Kong. 

While The Australian understands the letters were received by Mr Marape’s office, his spokesman said the Prime Minister was “unaware of such projects” . 

“However, if a foreign investor wants to come to PNG with multimillion kina investments, PNG will not stop them, on condition that all our laws are complied with and local Papua New Guineans benefit from these types of projects ,” the spokesman said. 

The proposal was being floated at the same time as China’s Fujian Zhonghong Fishery Company was seeking support for its “comprehensive multifunctional fishery industrial park” , which was the subject of a November memorandum of understanding between the Chinese and PNG governments.

column31: Not sure if this is the correct place to be asking this, but here goes. I am worried about my daughter. She is 7 and an only child. She goes to a Welsh medium school. She is still not independently reading or writing (in any language). I got a personal tutor who before lockdown came to the house once a week for an hour to try and help with her English literature and reading. She suggested that she has a visual dyslexia which is why she is not picking things up quickly. The one to one help was amazing. It really brought her on, but then lockdown part 2 happened. During the lockdowns, we have been struggling (like many are). Her behaviour is very difficult. She will cry and moan through every task. I notice through the Microsoft team meetings she has every day with the teacher and class, that she is already segregated from the other girls, who are all messaging each other during the lesson (not including her). She seems so behind that she doesnt even notice or read the messages and she certainly is not in a position to be able to join in. One thing that really upsets me is that she very rarely gets included in things. The children talk about what happened over the weekend and all the girls talked about a zoom party they had for one of the girls..my daughter was not invited. Instead she really wanted to tell them about her weekend, which was that she passed out for no known reason so we ended up in accident and emergency. But she didn't and instead ended up crying. She has strange obsessive behaviours, like she cannot be in a room with a tv turned off, or she has to turn phones over so that she cannot see the blank screen, she repeats her name under her breath, she hates buttons. I mean she will not come near me if I am wearing a cardigan with buttons on. She is addicted to her games console. If I try to take it away she cannot cope and starts screaming at me, crying uncontrollably. Everything is an uphill struggle with her and I am starting to wonder if I need to ask for professional help or assessment. I mentioned my concerns regarding the reading and writing to the school and they said that she is under the sensa team for help with her 'emotional literature'. She really does not like using the welsh medium and I feel this makes her muted at the school because they discourage the english language. Sounds to me the help she is receiving at the school is just to help cover up their segregation due to the language barriers....I just feel something is not adding up. I feel like I am failing her and I am getting angry with the school too. I do not want to label her and I have been just trying to tell myself that this must all be normal in order not to put any label or make a problem that is not there. I do not not know where to begin. Does she need english medium education? Does she need assessments for her development too? Or is it me? Am I just really shit at parenting? She is an only child so I have nothing else to compare things too. I do not socialise with the other mums, I find it very difficult. I have tried but they are so cliquey. I could go on, but this is the gist of things, sorry if it's all a bit disjointed.

Where the buck should stop.

Last year I ran as a candidate for the QLD state election.

I worked my arse off, spent hundreds upon hundred of hours and thousands of dollars from my own pocket that I really didn’t have to do so. I ran myself into the ground, physically, mentally and emotionally.

And it was worth it.

I stood up as an angry mum to show others that we can all make a stand. We, everyday mums and dads, can stand shoulder to shoulder with these evil, self centred, egotistical politicians to tell them we see them for who they are. Manipulative, lying bullies who don’t give a (enter your own expletive here) about us or our children.

And I got far more than I thought - a deeper look at the insane depth of corruption going on in the political game. I experienced it all first hand.

The schoolyard bullying tactics for starters. I knew it would be a rough ride, but I was not prepared for the absolute childishness that comes from politicians. This from the people that are supposed to be our spokespeople. Let me tell you - they might shake your hand and tell you exactly what you want to hear, they might even call you by your name. But they do 👏🏻 not 👏🏻 care 👏🏻 about you.

They’re only interested in what you can give them.

But now for the reason for this post - the money and the corruption.

Labor is rotten to the core. All the majors are. Labor, Liberal, Greens... they’re all the same. Absolute toxic poison to our country.

Worse.

They are criminals and should be charge with crimes against the Australian people for selling us out. More about that another time though...

Labor spent 7.8 MILLION dollars campaigning. At the very least. That’s just what they disclosed. They paid for “volunteers”. They bused them in. They even used work for the dole “volunteers”. But shhh 🤫, no one is supposed to know. 

That’s essentially all elections are. Marketing and manipulation. Using your money.

People would literally come over to me and tell me they aren’t voting for me, because they didn’t see me enough everywhere... you know, on signs and billboards and tv ads and newspapers... $$$

They wanted to vote for the party they thought had the best chance of getting in. You know, like placing a bet on the best horse. 🤯🤯🤯

My response probably should have been, “apologies, I didn’t have access to your money so I could market myself to you”. But I was honestly far too gobsmacked at the insane lack of intelligence far too many people seem to have... 🥴

Because that’s all politics is. A game. A corrupt, vile, sickening game. And it’s how we are programmed to see it - subconsciously. We are programmed to crave entertainment.

I say this all the time and I’ll say it again. The government, the entire system, needs such a huge overhaul. Every single one of those politicians need to be fired by the Australian people. The people they are supposed to be working for.

Instead, they are destroying this country. And we’re just sitting here letting them do it, looking for the next form of entertainment to make ourselves feel good.

We’re all guilty.

But now it’s time we get loud. ✊🏻⚔️

column36:
Today we want to talk about...gums! 👨‍⚕️
Everyone knows that taking good care of your teeth is vital for your oral health.  
But people tend to forget about one thing...the significant role of healthy gums and how much of an impact they have on our daily wellness!

Here are two main reasons why you ABSOLUTELY have to keep your gums healthy:   
1️⃣ Taking good care of your gums will prevent inflammation that is caused by bacteria sitting on the surface. 
When gums are inflamed, your body is more likely to get an infection through the blood flow.   
2️⃣ Gums provide support to your teeth and serve as shields to protect sensitive tissue underneath. 
If not treated properly, gum tissue develops little holes that are very easily accessible for bacteria. This lets bacteria from plaque and results in cavities and other complications.   

❗️Neglecting them can lead to unpleasant consequences, such as periodontal diseases and certain chronic illnesses. 

✔️Do not underestimate the importance of your gums health.
